commit.message:
Simplify isort config using 'profile = black'

isort now has builtin support for black through its "profiles" feature.

https://timothycrosley.github.io/isort/docs/configuration/profiles/#black
Add a version qualifier to isort

Adjust invocation of isort

isort v5 no longer accepts `--recursive`, instead it expects a path
and traverses that recursively.
Run tests against Django 3.1
Move import to top-level in example

Update isort configuration for compatibility with Black

https://github.com/psf/black/blob/master/docs/compatible_configs.md#isort
Fix typo in README
Use "primary" and "replica" terminology throughout docs
Remove unresolved ref
Move all docs to README.rst
Fix typo in CHANGES.rst
Prepare for the next release

Fix typo in setup.cfg

Fixes PyPI error:

    HTTPError: 400 Client Error: Invalid value for classifiers. Error:
    Classifier '[' is not a valid classifier. for url:
    https://upload.pypi.org/legacy/
Remove left in debug helper
Prepare for the next release
Fix typo
Fix error in README

Make DJANGO_REDIS_IGNORE_EXCEPTIONS more test friendly

Calculate the constants as the class is instantiated instead of import
time. This allows overriding the constant using Django's
override_setting without monkey patching the module.

Use native exception chaining

Removes custom implementation. Since Python 3, exception chaining it
builtin.
Remove duplicated omit exception code
Use TestCase.subTest in DjangoRedisConnectionStrings
Add entry to the changelog mentioning Jazzband
Remove support for unmaintained redis-py 2.X
Remove reference to previous maintainer from Travis
